sh personal name <i>Knud</i>, derived from Old Norse <i>Knútr</i> meaning ‘knot’. <i>Knud</i> was a Danish royal name, Latinized as <i>Canutus</i>."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Knutson was born about 1445, in Pytchley, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Cameron Knutson, was 37 and her mother, Beatrice York, was 37. She married Richard Isham about 1457, in Pytchley, Northamptonshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. She died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1445–":"umbes 1445–Surnud","1445–Female":"1445–Surnud","1438–1491":"1438–1491","1457–1492":"1457–1492","1460–1509":"1460–1509","1465–1505":"1465–1505","1473–1485":"1473–1485","1410–1445":"1410–1445","Cir 1457":"1457","1473":"1473","Abt 1445":"umbes 1445","1460":"1460","1492":"1492","1491":"1491","1457":"1457","1445":"1445","1465":"1465","1410":"1410","about 1457":"umbes 1457","1485":"1485","about 1433":"umbes 1433","1509":"1509","about 1460":"umbes 1460","1505":"1505","1438":"1438","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Northampton, Northamptonshire, England":"Northampton, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingd